tpm2-pkcs11
------------------------------------------
PKCS11 is a Public-Key Cryptography Standard that defines a standard method to
access cryptographic services from tokens/ devices such as hardware security
modules (HSM), smart cards, etc. In this project we intend to use a TPM2 device
as the cryptographic token.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.4-1
  libsqlite3-devel-3.49.1-1
  libsqlite3_0-3.49.1-1
  libssl-devel-3.0.17-1
  libssl3-3.0.17-1
  libtpm2_pkcs11-devel-1.9.1-1bl1
  libtpm2_pkcs11_1-1.9.1-1bl1
  libtss2-esys-devel-4.1.3-1bl1
  libtss2-esys0-4.1.3-1bl1
  libtss2-fapi1-4.1.3-1bl1
  libtss2-mu-devel-4.1.3-1bl1
  libtss2-mu0-4.1.3-1bl1
  libtss2-rc0-4.1.3-1bl1
  libtss2-tctildr0-4.1.3-1bl1
  libyaml0_2-0.2.5-1
  pkg-config-2.5.1-1

